//a variable is a location in which u store info
// a pointer is a variable that holds memory that points to location

int holds 4 bytes
bool 1 byte. false = 0, true = 1
float  -- 4 bytes
double -- 8 bytes
char (variable type -- 1 byte 
short (int) -- 2 bytes
long(int) -- 4 bytes

pointers -- 4 bytes

pointers enable pass by refernce. 
  -- pass by value is just a copy of the value. 

  pointers can be used to create and manipulate dynamic data structures (structures that can grow and shrink)